> > In short - these round bars are threaded on both ends and this is the
> > adjustment for the steering alignment. Once adjusted they are locked in
> > position by a locked nut.
> >
> > They may rock a slight bit as both ends are swivel joints (basically) to
> > use a non-technical term.
> >
> > They should not rotate alot though.
> >
> > A worn front end will have joints that have alot of slop in them.
> >
> > I'd say it is time to bring in a friend that can inspect the van or take
